===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|quaternioun}}, from {{der|en|LL.|quaterniō}}, from {{m|la|quaternī}}, ablative form of {{m|la|quater||four times}} + {{m|la|-iōn}}.<ref name="D.C-etym">{{R:Dictionary.com}}</ref><ref name="AHD-etym">''American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language'', fourth edition</ref><ref name="COED-etym&sense">''Concise Oxford English Dictionary'', eleventh edition</ref> The mathematics sense was {{coin|en|William Rowan Hamilton|nocap=1|in=1843}}.

